&lt;p&gt;When working in your tickets, TeamSupport supports full HTML editing, links, images, and even embedded video.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;One of our most popular features is the ability to insert a screen capture image directly into a ticket so that you can respond to a customer visually.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To insert an image you can use your favorite screen capture program (we like &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.techsmith.com/snagit.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;TechSmith&apos;s SnagIt&lt;/a&gt;) to take the picture, then edit it and copy the image to the clipboard.&amp;nbsp; Come back to TeamSupport and click on the Insert Pasted Image button, paste the image, then resize or crop it if needed and insert into the ticket.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The process looks something like this:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://app.teamsupport.com/dc/563584/images/635000893589450000.png&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Once you have this screen you can paste your image:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://app.teamsupport.com/dc/563584/images/635000893984110000.png&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When you paste the image, you&apos;ll have a screen like this where you can crop or resize if needed:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://app.teamsupport.com/dc/563584/images/635000894756210000.png&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The end result will be a ticket just like this one with embedded screen shots!&lt;/p&gt;
